selector_to_html = {"a[href=\"#reconstructed-movie-a-c\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Reconstructed movie - <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">A</span> <span class=\"pre\">*</span> <span class=\"pre\">C</span></code><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#reconstructed-movie-a-c\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1>", "a[href=\"#cnmf-object\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">CNMF Object<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#cnmf-object\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2>", "a[href=\"#checking-for-an-errors\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Checking for an errors<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#checking-for-an-errors\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>After a batch run, check the results to make sure the outputs do not contain a \u201ctraceback\u201d error.</p><p>An error-free processing run will yield \u201cNone\u201d in the cell below. Otherwise, an error will be printed.</p>", "a[href=\"#cnmf-outputs\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">CNMF outputs<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#cnmf-outputs\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>Similar to mcorr, you can use the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">mesmerize-core</span></code> API to fetch the outputs.</p><p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://mesmerize-core.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api/cnmf.html\">API reference for mesmerize-CNMF</a>\n<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://caiman.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Getting_Started.html#parameters\">API reference for caiman-CNMF</a></p>", "a[href=\"#contours-allow-you-to-plot-the-neurons-on-top-of-an-image\"]": "<h3 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Contours allow you to plot the neurons on top of an image<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#contours-allow-you-to-plot-the-neurons-on-top-of-an-image\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3><p>Returns: <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">(list</span> <span class=\"pre\">of</span> <span class=\"pre\">np.ndarray</span> <span class=\"pre\">of</span> <span class=\"pre\">contour</span> <span class=\"pre\">coordinates,</span> <span class=\"pre\">list</span> <span class=\"pre\">of</span> <span class=\"pre\">center</span> <span class=\"pre\">of</span> <span class=\"pre\">mass)</span></code></p>", "a[href=\"#run-the-cnmf-batch-items\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Run the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">cnmf</span></code> batch items<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#run-the-cnmf-batch-items\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1>", "a[href=\"#residuals-y-ac-bf\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Residuals - <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">Y</span> <span class=\"pre\">-</span> <span class=\"pre\">AC</span> <span class=\"pre\">-</span> <span class=\"pre\">bf</span></code><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#residuals-y-ac-bf\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>Mesmerize-core provides these outputs as lazy arrays. This allows you to work with arrays that would otherwise be hundreds of gigabytes or terabytes in size.</p>", "a[href=\"#reconstructed-background-b-f\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Reconstructed background - <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">b</span> <span class=\"pre\">*</span> <span class=\"pre\">f</span></code><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#reconstructed-background-b-f\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1>", "a[href=\"#data-path-setup\"]": "<h3 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Data path setup<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#data-path-setup\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3><p>Data setup is similar to <a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"motion_correction.html\"><span class=\"std std-doc\">motion_correction notebook</span></a>.</p><p>You can make a new batch named something like <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">cnmf.batch</span></code> just like you did for registration.</p>", "a[href=\"#run-cnmf\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Run CNMF<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#run-cnmf\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>The API is identical to running mcorr.</p><p>You can provide the mcorr item row to <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">input_movie_path</span></code> and it will resolve the path of the input movie from the entry in the DataFrame.</p>", "a[href=\"#a-note-on-strides-and-overlaps\"]": "<h4 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">A note on strides and overlaps<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#a-note-on-strides-and-overlaps\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h4><p>For registration, the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">strides</span></code> and <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">overlaps</span></code> have influence on the quality of the results as each patch is processed individually and merged.</p><p>For segmentation, the equivalent <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">stride</span></code> and <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">rf</span></code> parameters (yes, confusing) only influence the processing time and not the qualty of the result.</p>", "a[href=\"#cnmf\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">CNMF<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#cnmf\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Run the CaImAn <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">CNMF</span></code> algorithm using the mcorr output obtained in the last processing step.</p>", "a[href=\"#load-outputs\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Load outputs<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#load-outputs\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1>", "a[href=\"#segmentation\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Segmentation<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#segmentation\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>Extract neuronal locations and planar time-traces.</p>", "a[href=\"#exploring-spatial-components-neuron-masks-and-temporal-components-traces\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Exploring spatial components (neuron masks) and temporal components (traces)<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#exploring-spatial-components-neuron-masks-and-temporal-components-traces\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><h3>Feed a list of indices to get back specific traces of interest<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#feed-a-list-of-indices-to-get-back-specific-traces-of-interest\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3>", "a[href=\"#interactive-parameter-exploration\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Interactive Parameter Exploration<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#interactive-parameter-exploration\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><h2>Exploring spatial components (neuron masks) and temporal components (traces)<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#exploring-spatial-components-neuron-masks-and-temporal-components-traces\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><h3>Feed a list of indices to get back specific traces of interest<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#feed-a-list-of-indices-to-get-back-specific-traces-of-interest\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3>", "a[href=\"#using-lazyarrays\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Using LazyArrays<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#using-lazyarrays\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1>", "a[href=\"#caiman-docs-on-component-eval\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Caiman docs on component eval<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#caiman-docs-on-component-eval\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>https://caiman.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Getting_Started.html#component-evaluation</p><p>The quality of detected components is evaluated with three parameters:</p>", "a[href=\"#pull-contours-good-components\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Pull contours / good components<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#pull-contours-good-components\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>View the diffs</p>", "a[href=\"#initial-parameters\"]": "<h3 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Initial parameters<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#initial-parameters\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3><p>In general in Caiman, estimators are first initialized with a set of parameters, and then they are fit against actual data in a separate step.</p><p>In this section, we\u2019ll define a <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">parameters</span></code> object that will subsequently be used to initialize our different estimators.</p>", "a[href=\"motion_correction.html\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Registration<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#registration\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>Correct for rigid/non-rigid movement</p>", "a[href=\"#parameter-gridsearch\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Parameter Gridsearch<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#parameter-gridsearch\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>As shown for motion correction, the purpose of <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">mesmerize-core</span></code> is to perform parameter searches</p>", "a[href=\"#feed-a-list-of-indices-to-get-back-specific-traces-of-interest\"]": "<h3 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Feed a list of indices to get back specific traces of interest<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#feed-a-list-of-indices-to-get-back-specific-traces-of-interest\" title=\"Link to this heading\">#</a></h3>"}
skip_classes = ["headerlink", "sd-stretched-link"]

window.onload = function () {
    for (const [select, tip_html] of Object.entries(selector_to_html)) {
        const links = document.querySelectorAll(` ${select}`);
        for (const link of links) {
            if (skip_classes.some(c => link.classList.contains(c))) {
                continue;
            }

            tippy(link, {
                content: tip_html,
                allowHTML: true,
                arrow: true,
                placement: 'auto-start', maxWidth: 500, interactive: false,

            });
        };
    };
    console.log("tippy tips loaded!");
};
